OL,6,F"The defendant did lose his job due to
OL,7,Fthis offending and it was a great loss
OL,8,Fto him. However he didn't sit by and
OL,9,Fremain unemployed, but he secured
OL,10,Fstable employment again as a HGV
OL,11,Fdriver. His family are dependent on
OL,12,Fhim financially. There are three
OL,13,Fchildren aged eight, 12, and 10.
OL,15,F"His partner is a full time carer for
OL,16,Ftheir 10-year-old so she doesn't work.
OL,17,FThe family are completely reliant on
OL,18,Fhim to survive. He also supports the
OL,19,Ffamily in an emotional way."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
