OL,3,CMan stole #28k worth of cereal and
OL,4,Csaid he had given it to foodbank
OL,6,F"You have come perilously close to
OL,7,Fgoing to custody today. What has saved
OL,8,Fyou is the fact that your family is
OL,9,Freliant on you and your income. But
OL,10,Fit's a fact you should reflect upon
OL,11,Fthat you had no thought for your
OL,12,Ffamily when you chose to act as
OL,13,Fselfishly as you did in stealing a
OL,14,Fshipment from your employers."
OL,16,FHe sentenced Wyatt, of Lund Avenue,
OL,17,FRadcliffe, to two years in prison,
OL,18,Fsuspended for 18 months. He ordered
OL,19,Fhim to carry out 20 rehabilitation
OL,20,Fdays, 100 hours of unpaid work, and to
OL,21,Fpay #400 in court costs.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/9
